The paper deals with a graph theory problem, specifically the Directed Disjoint Paths problem, and proposes a novel relaxation of the problem called the Disjoint Enough Directed Paths problem. The paper also studies the parameterized complexity of the problem for various choices of parameters. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
